  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When spending a move action to move as part of rapid assault, the armiger may divide her movement up between the triggering action and the granted bonus attacks. This movement provokes attacks of opportunity as normal. Additionally, if she does not have a move action available, the armiger may still move up to her speed as if she spent a move action. Doing so makes the armiger staggered on her next turn even if she would normally be immune to the staggered condition.</p>\n",
